This paper discusses the theory and practice of data citation, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which focuses on the management, organization, and dissemination of digital information, including data sets. The paper also discusses issues related to information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR), which are all relevant to data citation.
